explanation:
Each listed symbol is required because MISRA C’s for-loop well-formedness must be checked not only in the target function body but also in the behaviour of any functions/macros called from it. Specifically:

- OS_CHECK_POINTER: Macro invoked at function entry; it may expand into code (or calls) that contains for loops or side-effecting expressions relevant to clause analysis.
- OS_CHECK_SIZE: Same reason as OS_CHECK_POINTER — it may expand into code that contains loops or calls that affect loop-well-formedness.
- OS_printf: Present in the static call graph and potentially invoked (directly or via the macros); its implementation must be examined for any for-loops (and side-effects) because calls to it are inside the target’s execution path.
- OS_ObjectIdGetById: Direct callee of OS_TimedWrite; its body must be inspected for for-loops or modifications to objects that could be used as loop counters in callers.
- OS_ObjectIdTransactionInit: Callee of OS_ObjectIdGetById; included because nested callees’ for-loops (or side-effects on objects) are part of the target’s behaviour.
- OS_ObjectIdToArrayIndex: Callee of OS_ObjectIdGetById; may contain loops or modify objects relevant to loop control.
- OS_ObjectIdConvertToken: Callee of OS_ObjectIdGetById; included for the same nested-behaviour reason.
- OS_ObjectIdTransactionCancel: Callee of OS_ObjectIdGetById; included for nested-call analysis.
- OS_GenericWrite_Impl: Direct callee that performs the actual write; its implementation (and any loops in it) must be checked because it is executed within OS_TimedWrite.
- OS_ObjectIndexFromToken: Callee of OS_GenericWrite_Impl; its loops/side-effects may impact loop-counter usage in higher-level functions.
- OS_SelectSingle_Impl: Callee of OS_GenericWrite_Impl; included because internal loops/side-effects are part of the called behaviour.
- OS_ObjectIdRelease: Direct callee used for cleanup; its implementation must be checked for loops or side-effects that occur within OS_TimedWrite’s execution.
- OS_ObjectIdTransactionFinish: Callee of OS_ObjectIdRelease; included because its internals contribute to the behaviour invoked by OS_TimedWrite.
- UT_Stub_RegisterReturnType, UT_Stub_RegisterContextWithMetaData, UT_ExecuteBasicHandler, UT_Stub_GetReturnValuePtr: These unit-test/stub framework symbols appear in the static call graph for OS_TimedWrite (instrumentation/stub paths). If the build under analysis includes these stub calls, their implementations must be checked for any for-loops or side-effects because they are part of the target’s observed behaviour.

In summary, any function or macro called (directly or indirectly) from OS_TimedWrite can contain for-loops or side-effects that affect compliance with the MISRA for-loop rule, so the above symbols are the close set that must be inspected to determine if OS_TimedWrite (including the behaviour of its callees) violates the rule.
